com.argox.sdk.barcodeprinter.emulation.pplz

Class PPLZ_SetUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.argox.sdk.barcodeprinter.emulation.pplz.PPLZ_SetUtil

  • public class PPLZ_SetUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides methods for setting programs related to the printer parameters of the PPLZ emulator. This class is used in PPLZ class.

      • setMirror

        public final void setMirror(boolean isMirror)
                     throws BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to enable or disable mirror mode.

        This function regardless of been called at any location in the program, will proceed mirror print or normal print on all text, bar codes, or patterns are according to the setting.

        If the function has been called multiple times, the printing will be effected according to the last setting.

        Parameters:
        isMirror - [in] Whether to print in the mirror mode. 'true' is the mirror mode; 'false' is the normal mode; default value is 'false'.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.

        public final void setBackfeed(int length)
                       throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                              BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to set the backfeed distance of the label before printing. This function will feed the label. After printing, the label will be fed forward to the specified length, and the specified length is the set value.
        Parameters:
        length - [in] Feed length. Range: -255~255; unit: pixels.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.

                       throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                              BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to set the printing temperature of the printer head.
        Parameters:

To get better printing quality, various factors have to be considered, for example: printing speed, media types, ribbon types (wax, semi-resin and resin), image pattern, ... etc.

        baudRate - [in] Baud rate. Supports: 600, 1200, 2400, 4800, 9600, 19200, 38400, 57600, 115200.

        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.

      • setPrintOut

        public final void setPrintOut(int totalLabel,
                              int pauseCutValue,
                              int copies,
                              boolean usePauseCut)
                       throws BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException,
                              BarcodePrinterGeneralException
        This function is used to output the print command and the number of prints to a temporary area. This is equivalent to the end of a label format content. So, after the function call been completed, there will be the beginning of a new label format content. When you need to output multiple label formats content, you can use combined mode as: PPLZ_SetUtil.setPrintOut + ... + PPLZ_SetUtil.setPrintOut + PPLZ_IOUtil.printOut.
        Parameters:
        totalLabel - [in] Total number of pages to be printed. The value should be "copies of label" * "number of serialization"; range: >= 1.
        pauseCutValue - [in] The number of label to pause and cut. Range: >= 0.
        copies - [in] The number of copies to be printed for every serial value. Range: >= 0.
        usePauseCut - [in] Whether to pause or cut after 'pauseCutValue' is reached. 'true' is to pause; 'false' is not to pause.
        Throws:
        BarcodePrinterIllegalArgumentException - Invalid parameter or parameter is out of the valid range.
        BarcodePrinterGeneralException - General error, byte array operation error.
        See Also:
        PPLZ_IOUtil.printOut()
